com.cyber2.api.lib.client.writer

Class TagWriterAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cyber2.api.lib.client.AbstractClientAdapter
      • com.cyber2.api.lib.client.writer.AbstractWriterAdapter
        • com.cyber2.api.lib.client.writer.AbstractBaseWriterAdapter<Tag,String>
          • com.cyber2.api.lib.client.writer.TagWriterAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Identifiable<Tag,String>, UrlTypeable, GroupAssociateWritable<String>, IndicatorAssociateWritable<String>

    public class TagWriterAdapter
extends AbstractBaseWriterAdapter<Tag,String>
implements UrlTypeable, GroupAssociateWritable<String>, IndicatorAssociateWritable<String>
    TagWriterAdapter is the primary writer adapter for all Tag level objects. It uses the Connection object to execute requests against the RequestExecutor object. The responsibility of this class is to encapsulate all the low level ThreatConnect API calls specifically targeted at data under the Tag type.
    Author:
    dtineo
